abouts.en_US:
The Challenger Series (CS) is the birthplace of future esports champions in North America and Europe. As a primary path for players to join the premier LCS, competition in the CS is fierce. The Challenger series is comprised of six teams facing each other team in a Best of 3 double round robin format.

Playoff Format

Challenger Series playoffs are comprised of four teams in a seeded, Best of 5 single elimination playoff.

NA CS: Airs every Thursday at 5:00pm Pacific / 02:00 Berlin Time

Qualifier Format

To qualify for the Challenger Series, teams must advance through their regional Open Qualifier Bracket before the split starts. You can find more information about the Open Qualifiers here.

How to watch

You can watch the Challenger Series live on lolesports or on our spoiler-free VODs page once each match is finished. The full match schedule is available here.

bios.en_US:
We are Apex - hear us roar. Say hello to the newest team to enter the LCS. Even though this is a fresh team, there are some experienced players on the roster, and theyve been working hard to make it from the Challenger circuit into the LCS. Apex has been playing together since the beginning of 2016, and they actually have an advantage in some of the older LCS teams in that aspect - new recruits aside, they know each other and have built up their synergy. The team even took an intensive boot camp in Korea before preparing for the Summer Split. With a veteran coach in their corner, and former LCS players looking to take another shot at the big leagues, Apex Gaming are bound to be an exciting team to watch.

Coach: Brandon Saintvicious DiMarcio
